AMAZULU have started bolstering their squad ahead of the 2019/2020 season with the signing of striker Lehlohonolo Majoro. Last season Cavin Johnson charges lost the services of South American forward Emiliano Tade to Mamelodi Sundowns in the January transfer window.The club confirmed the arrival of New Zealand striker Andre de Jong last month, and they have now roped in their former striker Majoro whose contract was not renewed by Bidvest Wits. The 32-year-old has penned a two-year deal with Usuthu and sees him return to the club where he made his professional debut back in 2010.  